dian/Pix/pictures/2015/1/9/1420764242097/ec588c57-1af6-4808-bd2e-2b16c1addf78-460x241.png\" alt=\"High5 Dream Team jersey\" width=\"460\" height=\"241\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\">The High5 Dream Team jersey.</span> <span class=\"element-image__credit\">Photograph: High5 Dream Team</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <p>Gilmore came up with the idea of a top-flight domestic team after discussions with CA during last year’s world road championships.</p> <p>“I said ‘listen, I have 15 women wanting to ride for my team (Wiggle Honda), can you please give me some advice on who has the talent, who we should be looking at’,” Gilmore told reporters.</p> <p>“During these conversations, I realised there was a question mark over what was happening at CA the following year - the funding situation might not be as strong as it has been.</p> <p>“There was a pool of these athletes who CA have recommended - if we can do something, get some funding, let’s get them together.”</p> <p>“(They) are the best that Australia has who aren’t already in pro teams.”</p> <p>Gilmore has also committed to sending six riders to Europe for a six-week training and racing trip.</p> <p>“That was what the national program was doing in the past,” she said.</p> <p>Gilmore added that the six riders would not necessarily come from the High5 squad.</p> <p>One of the new team’s leaders is Kimberley Wells, who on Wednesday night regained the national criterium championship.</p> <p>The team members are Wells, Rebecca Wiasak, Jess Mundy, Georgia Baker, Tessa Fabri, Kendelle Hodges, Ellen Skerett and Sam de Riter.<br /></p> <p>Lauren Perry will also be involved as an associate scholarship holder.</p> <p>“What we’re going to do is create an environment for these athletes where they have the best equipment, the best everything,” Gilmore said.</p> <p>“We will ask the world of them in return as professional athletes.</p> <p>“These athletes will be supported better than any other domestic-based athletes have been supported before.”</p>","headline":"New Australian women's cycling team High5 Dream Team launched","trailText":"Domestic team set up by Wiggle Honda owner aims to help local riders bridge gap to professional racing in Europe despite suspension of Cycling Australia funding","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2015/1/9/1420764164656/37a0e8bf-fa35-4d6c-a883-39bfe32134b9-140x84.jpeg","wordcount":"426","commentable":"true","productionOffice":"AUS","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2015-01-12T11:00:00+11:00"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2015/jan/09/new-australian-womens-cycling-team-high5-dream-team-launched","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/sport/2015/jan/09/new-australian-womens-cycling-team-high5-dream-team-launched","tags":[{"id":"sport/cycling","webTitle":"Cycling","type":"keyword","sectionId":"sport","sectionName":"Sport","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/cycling","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/sport/cycling","references":[]},{"id":"sport/australia-sport","webTitle":"Australia sport","type":"keyword","sectionId":"sport","sectionName":"Sport","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/australia-sport","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/sport/australia-sport","references":[]},{"id":"sport/sport","webTitle":"Sport","type":"keyword","sectionId":"sport","sectionName":"Sport","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/sport","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/sport/sport","references":[]},{"id":"type/article","webTitle":"Article","type":"type","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/articles","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/type/article","references":[]},{"id":"tone/news","webTitle":"News","type":"tone","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/tone/news","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/tone/news","references":[]}],"references":[],"elements":[{"id":"00e730550f9880d02e32211adc4cbe3685916eaf","relation":"main","type":"ima