nDate":"2015-01-05T11:25:46Z","sectionName":"Sport","sectionId":"sport","id":"sport/2015/jan/05/bradley-wiggins-team-sky-contract-extension","fields":{"shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/44thf","standfirst":"• 2012 Tour de France champion to race Paris-Roubaix<br />• Wiggins prepares to bid farewell to road racing at Paris-Roubaix Classic<br />• <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2014/sep/14/bradley-wiggins\" title=\"\">Wiggins will then focus on 2016 Rio Olympics</a>","hasStoryPackage":"false","body":"<p>Sir Bradley Wiggins’s final season in top-flight road racing has begun to take shape after it was confirmed that he will race until the end of April this year for Team Sky, his sixth season with the British team, and that the Paris-Roubaix Classic on 12 April will be his principal early-season target.</p> <p>Wiggins said in a statement on the Team Sky website, “Everyone knows what this team means to me so I’m really pleased to extend my contract until the end of April 2015. I’ve been with Team Sky from the start. I’ve had some amazing experiences during that time and I hope there are a few more to come.</p> <p>“Paris-Roubaix is a special race for me and I’m determined to give it another go in Team Sky colours. It’s one of the toughest races in the calendar and my aim is to improve on my finish last year. After that I can focus fully on preparing for the Rio Olympics in 2016.”</p> <p>Wiggins’s goal is to finish his career at Rio, if possible riding the team pursuit for Great Britain. Along the way he is likely to make an attempt on the World Hour Record, which has been provisionally pencilled in for the end of June, <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2014/aug/26/bradley-wiggins-world-hour-record-2015\" title=\"\">he told the Guardian in August</a>.</p> <p><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2014/apr/13/bradley-wiggins-paris-roubailles-cycling\" title=\"\">Wiggins finished ninth in Paris-Roubaix in 2014</a>, the best performance by a Tour de France winner since Greg LeMond finished in the same position in 1992.</p> <p>No Tour victor has won the cobbled Classic since Bernard Hinault in 1981. “It would be incredible [to win], but I’m not quite thinking at the moment about that,” he told Sky Sports. ”I’m just concentrating on the training and the process of getting there. Just to be part of that race and to be there again in the final would be an amazing way to go out. It was an incredible feeling last year to just be there with some of those guys that were there in the final and to do that again would be an amazing thing.”</p> <p>Wiggins has raced for Team Sky since the team’s inception in 2010 and has been their most successful rider since then, winning the Tour de France, Dauphiné Libéré, Tour of Romandie and Paris-Nice “race to the sun” in 2012, along with the world time-trial championship and Tour of California in 2014.</p> <p>He also held the pink leader’s jersey at the Giro d’Italia, and the leader’s jersey at the Vuelta a España for the British team, and won races as diverse as the prologue time trial in the Giro, the Tour of Britain and British national titles at road race and time trial while wearing their distinctive black jersey with light blue stripe.</p> <p>After his contract with Sky finishes at the end of April, Wiggins is expected to transfer to a new squad registered at UCI Continental level, provisionally entitled “Team Wiggo”, which is being set up to enable him and other prospective Great Britain team pursuiters to race on the road while preparing for Rio.</p> <p>Details on “Team Wiggo” are sparse at present, although much of the lineup has filtered out. It will include pursuiters Owain Doull, Mark Christian, Andy Tennant and Steven Burke, with Jon Dibben another possible. The directeur sportif will be former professional Simon Cope, who has been involved with the Great Britain team for several years. It seems likely that it will be backed by Sky, although UCI rules mean it cannot take Sky’s name as its official title. There are indications that the team may race for the first time without Wiggins – in the Challenge Mallorca at the end of January.</p>","headline":"Bradley Wiggins signs final contract extension with Team Sky","trailText":"Sir Bradley Wiggins has signed a contract extension with Team Sky up to and including the Paris-Roubaix race in April 2015<br />","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Sport/Pix/columnists/2015/1/5/1420457061007/Bradley-Wiggins-006.jpg","wordcount":"607","commentable":"true","byline":"William Fotheringham","productionOffice":"UK","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2015-01-08T11:25:48Z"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2015/jan/05/bradley-wiggins-team-sky-contract-extension","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/sport/2015/jan/05/bradley-wiggins-team-sky-contract-extension","tags":[{"id":"sport/bradleywiggins","webTitle":"Sir Bradley Wiggins","type":"keyword","sectionId":"sport","sectionName":"Sport","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/bradleywiggins","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/sport/bradleywiggins","references":[]},{"id":"sport/team-sky","webTitle":"Team Sky","type":"keyword","sectionId":"sport","sectionName":"Sport","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/team-sky","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/sport/team-sky","references":[]},{"id":"sport/cycling","webTitle":"Cycling","type":"keyword","sectionId":"sport","sectionName":"Sport","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/cycling","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/sport/cycling","references":[]},{"id":"sport/sport","webTitle":"Sport","type":"keyword","sectionId":"sport","sectionName":"Sport","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/sport","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/sport/sport","references":[]},{"id":"tone/news","webTitle":"News","type":"tone","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/tone/news","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/tone/news","references":[]},{"id":"type/articl