s Ruta del Sol stage race, Porte had to pull out midway through the Tirreno-Adriatico because of illness.</p> <p>He would eventually abandon his plans to ride at the Giro.</p> <p>Porte then took over leadership of the Sky team when Froome had to pull out of the Tour de France. At one point he was third overall in the race, but again ill health dogged him and he finished 23rd.</p> <p>Porte, who also finished third behind Gerrans at the 2012 nationals, will not have to worry about the Orica-GreenEDGE rider this year.</p> <p>Gerrans broke his collarbone in a pre-Christmas training crash, ruling him out of title defences at the road nationals and the Tour Down Under.</p> <p>His absence clearly opens the race up for Porte and Evans, who will retire in early February.</p> <p>“I love the Buninyong course and I don’t think that GreenEDGE has got quite the numbers they’ve had in other years,” he said.</p> <p>“It would be very nice to have a podium like we had this year and anybody that wins on that circuit is a worthy winner.</p> <p>“So it’s a big goal to go there and try and take that jersey.”</p>","headline":"Richie Porte targeting Giro and Australian national championships","trailText":"Australian cyclist hopes to lead British Sky team at first grand tour of the year and is optimistic about chances of doing it while wearing national champion’s jersey","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/12/30/1419913991599/ac68c306-49d2-4084-8751-343f389f46d3-140x84.jpeg","wordcount":"413","commentable":"true","byline":"Australian Associated Press","productionOffice":"AUS","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2015-01-02T15:30:00+11:00"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2014/dec/30/richie-porte-targeting-giro-and-australian-national-championships","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/sport/2014/dec/30/richie-porte-targeting-giro-and-australian-national-championships","tags":[{"id":"sport/cycling","webTitle":"Cycling","type":"k