rans breaks collarbone","webPublicationDate":"2014-12-22T01:40:48Z","sectionName":"Sport","sectionId":"sport","id":"sport/2014/dec/22/simon-gerrans-breaks-collarbone","fields":{"shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/44chn","standfirst":"<p>Orica-GreenEdge cyclist suffered injury in crash while riding his mountain bike and will miss Australian road championships and Tour Down Under</p>","hasStoryPackage":"false","body":"<p>Australian cycling star Simon Gerrans has broken his left collarbone in training, ruining his home season.</p> <p>The Orica-GreenEdge rider was to undergo surgery on Monday afternoon, a day after crashing while riding his mountain bike.</p> <p>The accident means Gerrans will not defend his Australian road championships and Tour Down Under titles early next year.</p> <p>The accident occurred while Gerrans was training on a mountain bike in Victoria.</p> <p>“About half way through my mountain bike ride I became a little unstuck, came down and landed pretty heavily on my left side,” he explained.</p> <p>“I knew straight away as I hit the ground that I had broken my left collarbone.</p> <p>“From there I had a little bit of a walk to get down to a point where I was picked up by a four-wheel drive and went directly to Mansfield hospital to get cleaned up and have the x-ray to confirm.”</p> <p>A <a href=\"http://www.greenedgecycling.com/news/classics-focus-for-gerrans-after-training-crash\">statement on Orica-GreenEdge’s website</a> said the rider would target a return for the spring classics, which begin in March.</p> <p>“Unfortunately it doesn’t matter how well the recovery goes from here, I don’t think I am going to be in any condition to be racing at a high level in January,” Gerrans said.</p> <p>“With that in mind I think it is better to take my time, make sure the recovery goes well and get all the rehab done so I don’t have any ongoing issues.</p> <p>“It’s a big blow not to be able to line up in the national championships and Tour Down Under and defend my titles. They are races that I really enjoy and I know how important they are to the team.</p> <p>“Looking on the bright side, what it does do, is force a bit of a break now and mean that I can work towards some goals later in the season and be a lot fresher.” </p>","headline":"Simon Gerrans breaks collarbone","trailText":"Orica-GreenEdge cyclist suffered injury in crash while riding his mountain bike and will miss Australian road championships and Tour Down Under","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/12/22/1419212406955/b785f6e0-3e53-484a-84dd-75ea50c370aa-140x84.jpeg","wordcount":"309","commentable":"true","byline":"Staff and agencies","productionOffice":"AUS","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-12-25T12:45:00+11:00"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2014/dec/22/simon-gerrans-breaks-collarbone","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/sport/2014/dec/22/simon-gerrans-breaks-collarbone","tags":[{"id":"sport/cycling","webTitle":"Cycling","type":"keyword","sectionId":"sport","sectionName":"Sport","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/cycling","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/sport/cycling","references":[]},{"id":"sport/australia-sport","webTitle":"Australia sport","type":"keyword","sectionId":"sport","sectionName":"Sport","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/australia-sport","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/sport/australia-sport","references":[]},{"id":"sport/sport","webTitle":"Sport","type":"keyword","sectionId":"sport","sectionName":"Sport","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/sport","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/sport/sport","references":[]},{"id":"type/article","webTitle":"Article","type":"type","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/articles","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/type/article","references":[]},{"id":"tone/news","webTitle":"News","type":"tone","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/tone/news","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/tone/ne